 Broadly speaking, syntactic pattern discovery techniques are used for finding
 patterns in data that can be projected into streams of primitives.
 This problem is roughly analogous to finding the syntax rules in a book
 of an unknown language.
 In the context of DNA microarray data, this book may consist of expression
 levels of thousands of genes.
 Or, in clinical data, this book may contain answers to lifestyle questions
