\begin_inset Formula $S=\{s_{1},s_{2},\ldots,s_{n}\}$
\end_inset

, and an integer 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

, find all patterns which occur at least 
\begin_inset Formula $K$
\end_inset

 times in 
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

.
 We call this set of patterns 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}=\{p_{1},p_{2},\ldots,p_{m}\}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}$
\end_inset

 is a pattern in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{C}$
\end_inset

.
 Each pattern 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}$
\end_inset

 defines a language 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}(p)$
\end_inset

 which is the set of all strings that can be derived from 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 A sequence 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

matches
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}$
\end_inset

 if it contains a substring that belongs to 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{L}(p_{i})$
\end_inset

.
 For example, if 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}=$
\end_inset


\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\family typewriter
KYLE
\family default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, then the sequences 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\family typewriter
GOTOBEDKYLE
\family default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\family typewriter
WRITEYOURPROPOSALKYLE
\family default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset


\family typewriter
GOODBOYKYLEWRITE
\family default

\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 all match 
\begin_inset Formula $p_{i}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

